business_analysis.business_domain: Local peer-to-peer marketplace platform enabling individuals to buy and sell used and new items within their communities
business_analysis.business_model: Commission-based marketplace with revenue from listing promotions, featured placements, shipping services, and potential transaction fees on sales
key_products_services: Mobile and web marketplace platform for local buying/selling
business_analysis.target_customers: Individual consumers looking to buy or sell secondhand goods locally, including casual sellers decluttering homes, bargain hunters, collectors, and small resellers

key_entities.name: users
key_entities.description: Individual buyers and sellers on the platform with profiles, ratings, and transaction history

key_entities.name: listings
key_entities.description: Items posted for sale with photos, descriptions, prices, and location data

key_entities.name: categories
key_entities.description: Product taxonomy including Electronics, Vehicles, Home & Garden, Clothing, Baby & Kids, etc.

key_entities.name: transactions
key_entities.description: Completed sales between buyers and sellers

key_entities.name: messages
key_entities.description: In-app communications between buyers and sellers

key_entities.name: locations
key_entities.description: Geographic data for local marketplace matching (cities, neighborhoods, zip codes)

key_entities.name: reviews
key_entities.description: User ratings and feedback after transactions

key_entities.name: promotions
key_entities.description: Paid listing enhancements and featured placements

data_products.name: Seller Dashboard
data_products.description: Analytics for sellers showing listing views, messages received, and sales performance

data_products.name: Search & Discovery Algorithm
data_products.description: Location-based matching and ranking system for connecting buyers with relevant local listings

data_products.name: Trust & Safety Scoring
data_products.description: User reputation and fraud detection system based on transaction history and behavior

primary_use_cases: Marketplace health monitoring and liquidity analysis
Fraud detection and trust & safety monitoring
Revenue optimization from promotions and fees
business_questions: What is our marketplace liquidity by category and geography?
Which categories have the highest conversion rates and fastest time-to-sale?
What are the pricing trends for popular items across different markets?
How do promoted listings perform vs organic listings?
What is the buyer-to-seller ratio in each geographic market?
Which user cohorts have the highest lifetime transaction value?
What search terms have low result quality or high abandonment?
How does message response time correlate with transaction completion?
What are the characteristics of our most successful power sellers?
Which markets are underserved and represent growth opportunities?
What fraud patterns can we detect in user behavior?
How does seasonal demand vary by category and location?
demo_opportunities: Build marketplace health dashboard showing GMV, active listings, and transaction velocity by category
Create geographic heat maps showing market density and opportunity zones
Demonstrate pricing analytics showing competitive pricing insights by category and location
Show user cohort analysis tracking buyer/seller behavior and retention over time
Build conversion funnel analysis from search to message to transaction
Create seller performance scorecards with benchmarking against category averages
Demonstrate fraud detection using behavioral pattern analysis
Show A/B test results for promoted listing effectiveness
Build category trend analysis showing emerging vs declining product categories
Create real-time operational dashboard for trust & safety team

notable_features: Strong emphasis on local, in-person transactions
Wide category diversity from vehicles to collectibles
Competes with Facebook Marketplace, Craigslist, and Mercari
Heavy reliance on location-based matching algorithms
Trust and safety critical to platform success
Network effects drive value - more buyers attract sellers and vice versa
Seasonal patterns evident in categories like vehicles, outdoor equipment, and clothing
